          "3866 ASSISTments learners, 332 Statics learners",
          "ASSISTments, Statics",
          "Sequence of Questions, LMS logs",
          "[Exercise Tag, Correctedness, First Response Time, Attempt Count, First Action]",
          "Previous DKT models only consider Question/Skill and correctedness as individual features.",
          "Authors look to improve DKT by adding additional feature sets and an Undercomplete Auto-Encoder to reduce dimensionality and improve training speed.",
          "Features are represented as a one-hot encoded sparse vector.",
          "DKT, DKT_time/correct, DKT_time/correct_AE, DKT_time/correct_time_action_attempt, DKT_time/correct_time_action_attempt_AE, DKT_time/correct_time/skill_time_action_attempt_AE,",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "AST\n{AUC: 0.867 - DKT_time/correct_time_action_attempt_AE, DKT_time/correct_time/skill_time_action_attempt_AE, R2 Score: 0.412 - DKT_time/correct_time/skill_time_action_attempt_AE}\n\nStatics\nAST\n{AUC: 0.74 - DKT_time/correct_time_action_attempt_AE, DKT_time/correct_time/skill_time_action_attempt_AE, R2 Score: 0.148 - DKT_time/correct_time_action_attempt_AE}",
          "Authors add multiple differetn types of feature sets to traditional DKT.\n\nResults from CV show that adding cross-features of skill/correctedness andd time/correctness tend to lead to better performance (both in terms of AUC and R2).\n\nThe presence of the Auto-Encoder also improves the performance of the model.",
          "No model optimization attempts. \n\nOnly focuses on DKT while not considering other viable approaches (at the time- e.g. BKT)."
        ]
      ],
